{"data_shared": "Adobe shares personal information within its family of companies and with other third-party data controllers with user consent or to provide requested products or services. This includes resellers, sales and advertising partners, retailers, advertisers, ad agencies, advertising networks and platforms, information service providers, fraud monitoring and prevention providers, and publishers. Also, Adobe discloses personal information for fraud prevention, safety, security purposes, and to companies that help run its business by processing personal information on behalf of Adobe.",
  "data_collected": "Adobe collects identifiers and contact information (name, email, telephone number, address, country), commercial and transaction information (payment/billing details, licenses, eligibility), professional, education, demographic information, analytics, electronic network activity (IP address, browser/device ID, browser extensions), and content including personal information sent/received using Adobe Services and Software. Additionally, Adobe collects biometric identifiers (faceprints, voiceprints) and geolocation data, where legally permitted.",
  "security_practices": "Adobe employs administrative, technical, and physical security controls where appropriate, such as encryption and 2-step verification. Personal information is stored on Adobe’s servers and those of companies Adobe engages to provide services. Data transfers across national borders comply with applicable laws, using mechanisms like European Commission approved Standard Contractual Clauses, and consent in certain cases."}

